channel.description:
Whenever i add ints to a regular PI server it gives this error
ItemDef.java:248: cannot find symbol symbol : variable anInt165 location: class ItemDef itemDef.anInt165 = 62737; ^ ItemDef.java:249: cannot find symbol symbol : variable anInt200 location: class ItemDef itemDef.anInt200 = 62753; ^ Note: client.java uses unchecked or unsafe operations. item.title: HELP OMFG No1 HAS ANSWERED ALL DAY PLEASE!11
item.dc:creator: @neonscapeftw neonscapeftw
item.description:
@neonscapeftw wrote:

[quote=“Epicmaul, post:1, topic:390218”]Whenever i add ints to a regular PI server it gives this error

ItemDef.java:248: cannot find symbol
symbol : variable anInt165
location: class ItemDef
itemDef.anInt165 = 62737;
^
ItemDef.java:249: cannot find symbol
symbol : variable anInt200
location: class ItemDef
itemDef.anInt200 = 62753;
^
Note: client.java uses unchecked or unsafe operations.
Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details.
2 errors
Press any key to continue . . .[/quote]
Use this template for adding items to PI:
case 13740:
itemDef.actions = new String[5];//menu
itemDef.actions[1] = “Wield”;
itemDef.modelID = 40921;//inventory/drop model
itemDef.modelZoom = 1483;//Model Zoom
itemDef.modelRotation1 = 396;//rotation 1
itemDef.modelRotation2 = 1050;//rotation 2
itemDef.modelOffset1 = -3;//model offset 1
itemDef.modelOffset2 = 4;//model offset 2
itemDef.maleEquip1 = 40939;//male wield ModelId
itemDef.femaleEquip1 = 40939;//female wield ModelId
itemDef.anInt188 = -1;//female sleeve
itemDef.anInt164 = -1;//male sleeve
itemDef.aByte154 = -10;
itemDef.aByte205 = -10;
itemDef.name = “Divine spirit shield”;//name
itemDef.description = “A spirit shield with a very powerful effect.”.getBytes();//name
break;

Im assuming that the 62737 is the model ID. You need to have it like this:

itemDef.maleEquip1 = 6273;//male wield ModelId itemDef.femaleEquip1 = 6273;//female wield ModelId
